

Oil prices rose Wednesday on falling gas inventories.

Light sweet crude for December settlement closed up 48 cents at 58.76 dollars a barrel on the New York Mercantile Exchange, touching 59.40 dollars in earlier trading.

Brent North Sea crude for December delivery rose 62 cents to 59. 46 dollars a barrel.

The Energy Information Administration reported Wednesday that crude oil inventories rose 1.3 million barrels to 336.0 million barrels last week. Gasoline inventories fell by 3.7 million barrels to 200.3 million barrels. The weekly report showed that refineries operated at 87.3 percent of capacity last week, down 0. 8 percent point from the prior week.

